Group
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="95.[123,651,310,935]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">DIAGNOSIS: Presumed synapomorphies of this group are the oviposition in bromeliads and the extreme reduction of webbing between toes II and III (Peixoto, 1987; Faivovich, 2002).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="95.[123,651,310,935]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
COMMENTS: The monophyly of this group was not tested by Faivovich (2002) because only one species of the group was available for his analysis, where it obtained as the sister taxon of all exemplars of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Amphibia" family="Hylidae" genus="Scinax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">S. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. For these two reasons, we continue recognizing this group until its monophyly is rigorously tested.
</paragraph>
